# Food Go/No-Go Task (PsychoPy)

## Overview
This project implements a Go/No-Go task using PsychoPy to study food-related inhibitory control.

Participants view images of food and must press the SPACEBAR for most stimuli (Go trials) but withhold responses when a No-Go cue appears.

The task includes:
- Food image presentation
- Go cue (green circle)
- No-Go cue (red circle)
- Reaction time recording

## Task Instructions
Participants are instructed to:

Press the SPACEBAR when they see a food image with a green circle.

Do NOT press the SPACEBAR when they see a food image with a red circle.

Responses and reaction times are recorded for each trial.

## Requirements

Python 3.x

Required packages:
- psychopy
- pandas

Install dependencies:

pip install psychopy pandas

## File Structure

Food-Choice-Task/
│
├── lists/
│   └── HF_LF_60.csv      # Stimulus list with food image names and fat category
│
├── stimuli/
│   └── food_images/      # Food stimulus images
│
└── README.md             # Project documentation

## Running the Experiment

1. Open the script in PsychoPy Coder.
2. Update the stimulus file paths if necessary.
3. Run the script.
4. Enter participant information when prompted.

## Output

After the experiment finishes, a CSV file is saved containing:

- participant ID
- stimulus name
- trial type (Go / No-Go)
- participant response
- reaction time

Example output file:

participant1_gonogo.csv
